@btallman I played around with this and like it. However, can you address the comments above : 
- Show execution times for triggered dags as well
- Add a configuration variable to decide what is shown (Show Paused Dags/Hide Paused Dags) when the web app loads & default it to show paused DAGs.

@btallman Thanks for addressing 2 of the 4 issues, but there are still 2 remaining.

It seems the info_icon is wrapping to its own line. It should be `Last Run <info_icon>` not `Last Run <br><info_icon>` and the same problem happens near the values in the column. Can we set a fixed width to this column to keep the Date portion and time portion on different lines... that might fix it?

<img width="1260" alt="screenshot 2016-11-21 12 01 52" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/581734/20498523/5d1de674-afe2-11e6-9af4-4b51d933f136.png">

@sudowork Wow! Very interesting! Please open a JIRA for this. 
@poulainv This is definitely a regression. One idea is to 'Latest, allowing execution to proceed.' whenever a DAG is manually or externally triggered (i.e. not scheduled). I'll submit a fix for this!

@gwax FYI! Also, @btallman since you use trigger_dag, refer to @poulainv 's comment above.
